# Lasagna

> This best #lasagna has amazed everyone who's tried it

## Start the Sauce

> Use a large pot for this, as more ingredients come in later

- Ground Beef | 1 lb | 
- Italian Sausage | 1 lb | 
- Red Onion | 1/2 cup | Diced
- Garlic | 2 cloves | Minced

Cook until well browned

> Meanwhile, prepare the seasonings below

## Sauce Seasoning

- Sugar | 2 tbsp | 
- Parsley | 2 tbsp | 
- Salt | 1 tbsp | 
- Basil | 1.5 tsp | 
- Italian Seasoning | 1 tsp | 
- Fennel Seeds | 1/2 tsp | 
- Black Pepper (ground) | 1/4 tsp | 

Combine in small cup and set aside

## Finishing the Sauce

Wait until meat is well browned

- Tomato Basil Pasta Sauce | 26 oz | 
- Spicy Arrabiata Pasta Sauce | 26 oz | 
- Water | 1/2 cup | 

Sauce Seasoning from earlier

Combine above with meat, simmer for 90 minutes, covered

> Use this time to clean some of your dishes and put away spices (except the Parsley)

## Cooking the Noodles

- Lasagna Noodles (long) | 12 count | 

Cook in hot water according to package (regardless of "Ready to Bake" label)

Drain and rinse/soak with cold water to prevent sticking

## Prepare Cheeses

> Use a medium mixing bowl for this

- Ricotta Cheese | 1 lb | 
- Parsley | 2 tbsp | 
- Egg | 1 count | 
- Salt | 1/2 tsp | 

Mix above ingredients

## Assemble Lasagna

> Use an 11x15 baking dish if possible, or 9x13 (and you may discard some ingredients/layer).

Preheat oven to 375Â°F

Spread 1.5 cups meat sauce at bottom of baking dish

Lay 3 noodles along baking dish (4 if in smaller dish)

Spread ricotta cheese mixture

- Mozzarella Cheese (sliced) | 3/4 lb | 

Meat sauce

Repeat layers 4 times (3 if in smaller dish), ending with meat sauce

> Do NOT ðŸš¨ over-fill your dish, or ingredients will fall to your oven floor, burn, and start smoke alarms.

- Parmesan Cheese (shredded) | 3/4 cup | To top

Cover with tinfoil

Bake for 50 minutes

Remove foil after 25 minutes

